title: Days of the past;
author: Shand, Alexander Innes
snippet: Many a time have I gone for a solitary ramble with my rod up the Allan from * the Bridge ' to Greenloaning in the springtide, and pleasant sport one used to have in those days, though the trout were small.

author: Roger, James Cruikshank.
snippet: There is a place called Buttergask near Greenloaning in the same county.

title: Recollections of a Visit to Glasgow with the British Archæological Associations, August 27th to September 5th, 1888. With notes
author: Lambert, George
snippet: Taking train from Buchanan Street to Greenloaning, themembers drove through the grounds of Colonel DrummondMoray to Ardoch, and about an hour was spent in a persistentrainfall in an examination of the grass grown lines of theancient fortifications.
